messages.body:
$TSNP  $SPLK $MDB  $ESTC - Good morning traders. 

Investors are often skittish & for good reasons about trading OTC penny stocks. I think part of the reason has to do with the wild unpredictable & often unregulated nature of that market. 

Far too often the CEO’s of these tickers rely on fluff PR & exaggerated results to grow their companies.

This is why I always research before I recommend something in that market. 

My next strong buy alert is 🚨 $PLYZ  -  In my personal opinion Plyzer technologies is a giant hiding amongst a bunch of fluff. They are a data intelligence company for consumers and brands. They have massive contracts with medical giants like BAYER and HEEL. Before Covid they were trading around .30-50 cents and a year ago hit a high of .66 cents! At the current 52 week low of .0003 cents, this is a no brainer to buy and hold for the reverse movement up north. See you there hopefully with a few more zeros in your trading accounts. 

https://www.plyzertechnologies.com

Yuri

links.title: Why Elastic Stock Spiked Today
links.description: Shares of skyrocketed today after the company released its second-quarter results yesterday that beat analysts' consensus estimates. The tech stock was up by as much as 19.2% today and had gained 15.3% as of 11:55 a.m. EST. Elastic's revenue increased 43% year over year to $144.9 million, which was far better than the $130.5 million that analysts were estimating for the second quarter.
